One phenomenal entertainer, who can morph from street pimpin' to Harvard intelligence. I admire his brilliance, insight, cultural fortitude and Black Power awareness enough to want to inform the masses of the truth!

Another good one from Katt. It was a little sad when he talked about his troubles but as always, he found a way to make us laugh with him (even though he acknowledged the ones he knows were really laughing at him). He also foreshadowed all that has happened with police shootings without even being aware of it. Hes a comedic genius and seer of people and their ways for real. Ive always loved his standup and this one is no different. I hope he can sustain his current standing and bring us more great and meaningful comedy. Great video

I have seen all of Katt's comedy specials and I laugh at every single one of them. I saw this one on HBO the night that it premiered and I think that this is his funniest stand-up so far. Katt has been one of my favorite comedians since The Pimp Chronicles Pt. 1 and I can't wait to see what else he has in stored for us.

His intelligent, and insightful comedy reflects a witty perspective on our diverse society and evolving way of life. Approaching the breach of differences in our cultures, he is able to bridge the political and religious gaps by identifying the common funny bone that we all share. Mr. Williams delivers with honesty, a candid and uproarious account of his personal and legal struggles that have been in the media spotlight recently.  An artist and a champ, he has comeback better than ever, funny, smart and real.

Katt is totally priceless.  My favorite part of his routine is when he jokes about going to jail 5 times just because he is standing next to an even bigger celebrity than him.  It's so true it's funny.  Hilarious.  Because we all know the pain that has been endured, unfairly, by many Americans who become incarcerated for ridiculous reasons.  But instead of a Civil Rights movement, Katt puts it into his routine.  It's so true, and so sad, that normally we'd all be crying, but Katt takes our collective pain and makes a joke out of it, which helps us make it to another day.  And I've actually never heard him tell a bad joke, so picking my favorite one from this is tough, everything he says is funny.  He's A-1!  Better than watching a Batman movie.
Katt is very consistent; in my generation we would call him a real knee slapper.  As much as I have watched him there are always "I don't believe he said that" moments.
